smart Task & Notes Manager (Mobile App)

A productivity-focused mobile application that allows users to securely log in, manage personal tasks and notes, and track completion status.

This project is ideal because it:

Demonstrates authentication

Covers full CRUD

Uses real-world patterns

Is easy to extend if asked for “extra features”

Core Functional Requirements
1. Authentication (Mandatory)

Purpose: Proves you understand secure user access.

Features

User Registration (Sign Up)

User Login

Logout

Persisted login session

Implementation Options

Firebase Authentication (Email/Password)



Screens

Login Screen

Register Screen

2. Task Management (CRUD)

Purpose: Demonstrates Create, Read, Update, Delete operations.

Task Fields

Title

Description

Status (Pending / Completed)

Created Date

Updated Date

CRUD Actions

Create a task

View task list

View task details

Edit a task

Delete a task

3. Notes Module (CRUD)

Purpose: Shows multi-entity data handling.

Note Fields

Title

Content

Timestamp

Actions

Add note

View all notes

Edit note

Delete note

4. Additional Features 



✅ Task completion toggle
✅ Search tasks or notes
✅ Pull-to-refresh

✅ Dark mode
✅ Profile screen (view user info)

Technical Stack (Recommended)
Frontend

Expo (React Native)

TypeScript 

React Navigation

Axios or Fetch API

Backend

 – Firebase (Simplest)

Firebase Auth

Firestore database



JWT Authentication

App Screens Structure
/screens
 ├── LoginScreen.tsx
 ├── RegisterScreen.tsx
 ├── TaskListScreen.tsx
 ├── TaskDetailScreen.tsx
 ├── AddEditTaskScreen.tsx
 ├── NotesScreen.tsx
 ├── ProfileScreen.tsx

App Flow (High-Level)

User opens app

If not authenticated → Login/Register

On success → Dashboard (Task List)

User can:

Add/edit/delete tasks

Manage notes

Logout